# Configuration Pattern

Always use the centralized config system via the singleton `Config` class:

```python
from customer_support_agent.utils.config import get_config

config = get_config()
config.validate()

# Access YAML settings via dot notation (from config.yml)
config.model.name           # "claude-sonnet-4-5"
config.model.temperature    # 0.7
config.model.max_tokens     # 4096
config.project.name         # "Modular Agentic Chatbot Demo"
config.rag.collection_name  # "crm_knowledge_base"
config.demo.questions       # List of demo questions

# Access secrets (from .env)
config.anthropic_api_key    # ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
config.opik_api_key         # OPIK_API_KEY or COMET_API_KEY
config.opik_workspace       # OPIK_WORKSPACE
config.opik_project_name    # OPIK_PROJECT_NAME
```

## Configuring Opik

Use the built-in `configure_opik()` method which handles singleton configuration:

```python
config = get_config()
config.validate()
config.configure_opik()  # Only configures once, safe to call multiple times
```

**Important**: The config module loads `.env` at import time to ensure `OPIK_PROJECT_NAME` is available before Opik is imported anywhere.
